Defendant in custody.  
Defendant is sentenced to a total sentence of four (4) years, two (2) years initial confinement, followed by two (2) years extended supervision.  Conditions of extended supervision are:
1) Maintain full-time employment, schooling or combination thereof.
2) Pay supervision fees;
3) Submit to random urine screens and pay for same;
4) Comply with all assessments, treatment and counseling as deemed appropriate by the department's assessment process;
5) Comply with any alternative to revocation;
6) AODA assessment if deemed appropriate;
7) Pay costs of action;
Court finds the defendant is eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program and the Substance Abuse Program and gives him credit for 145 days time already served.  
ADA points out to the Court that the maximum sentence for this offense is 3 1/2 years..  
Court then changes the sentence to two (2) years initial confinement, followed by eighteen (18) months extended supervision.  
Court reads the Written Explanation of Determinate Sentence to the defendant.  
Court now modifies his second sentence to a total sentence of three and one-half (3 1/2) years.  Eighteen months initial confinment, followed by two years extended supervision.  
